article.description: Evan Gilyard scored 22 points and UTEP never trailed in its 73-44 win over Southern Miss on Saturday night.
article.headline: Gilyard scores 22 to help UTEP beat Southern Miss 73-44
article.linkText: Gilyard scores 22 to help UTEP beat Southern Miss 73-44
article.story: EL PASO, Texas -- Evan Gilyard scored 22 points and UTEP never trailed in its 73-44 win over Southern Miss on Saturday night. Omega Harris had 18 points and Isiah Osborne added 15 with eight rebounds for UTEP (10-18, 5-11 Conference USA). Southern Miss (13-17, 6-11) made just 5 of 31 (16.1 percent) from the field, including 1 of 15 from 3-point range, and trailed 38-15 at the break. Harris converted a 3-point play to make it 5-0 and Kobe Magee hit a 3 that pushed the lead to 10 points with nearly seven minutes left in the first half. Tyree Griffin made a jumper on Southern Miss' next possession, but Osborne answered with a 3 that sparked an 18-3 run -- including 10 points by Gilyard -- to close the half. Griffin led the Golden Eagles with 20 points on 8-of-12 shooting. The rest of the Southern Miss players made just 8 of 42 (19 percent) from the field.
